	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I haven't checked out those sources yet, but I was poking around in that site the other day.
<br />
<br />Another fascinating (to me) find in there was the "FC System Develop Kit".  It's a DOS program, copyright 1993.  It appears to be a hardware-linked debugger, and actually much more than that.  I only fooled around a bit with it, couldn't figure out how to load a program or edit memory (always went back to zero - I'm guessing it emulates very little and needs the actual NES hookup).
<br />
<br />It's not often to run across 15+ year old NES dev software..  Or NES dev anything, for that matter!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


